 "_meta": {
  "description": "Core-angular-momentum delta-LOD derived from the CFF core-flow models of Nilsson, Suttie, Troyano, Gillet, Aubert & Irback, \"Joint Bayesian inference of Earth's magnetic field and core surface flow on millennial timescales\" (jSEDI, doi:10.46298/jsedi.17320; data: EarthRef ERDA 2776, cff.models.zip). Computed from the posterior core-surface-flow samples (output/U, 500 samples) as LOD = 1.138*(t10 + (12/7)*t30) ms (Jault et al. 1988; Jackson et al. 1993; same convention as Rivera et al. 2026 Eq. 26), zonal toroidal coefficients at indices 0 and 8 of the toroidal-first Schmidt semi-normalized ordering. lod_ms = posterior mean (de-meaned over the full window); sigma_ms = posterior std. CFF.MP: 50-yr steps; CFF.NT: 100-yr steps; both 7000 BCE - 2000 CE.",
  "caution": "Posterior sigma (~2 ms) is comparable to the signal amplitude; pre-archeomagnetic epochs are constrained mainly by sedimentary data (lock-in smoothing). Treat spectral/phase conclusions before ~2000 BCE as low-confidence."
